  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve the Physical and Mental Health wellbeing of 9,324 Lebanese and 18,296 Syrian refugee beneficiaries through screening and vaccinating children against measles, and providing specialized Mental Health services in North Bekaa, Baalbeck, Arsal (IPMH).</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Relief International (RI) proposes the 12-month &#x201D;IPMH&#x201D; project that will provide immediate assistance to vulnerable populations in Arsal by 1) Responding to the gap in Mental Health services and, 2) Responding to the measles outbreak currently underway.  RI will provide increased access to mental health care in Arsal through two additional Clinical Psychologists and one Psychiatrist, based at the Al Amal Medical Center, but also with availability for home visits. Secondly, through the recruitment and comprehensive training of 16 Outreach Volunteers (OVs) RI will screen vaccination cards of Syrian and Lebanese children below the age of 15 years old and refer defaulters to supported health centers for vaccination.  OVs will be trained by the Ministry of Public Health (MOPH) on the Expanded Program for Immunization (EPI) protocol, Accelerated Immunization Activity (AIA), MOPH vaccination reporting system (MIRA), and Communication for Development (C4D). RI will also fill an unaddressed gap by ensuring increased community awareness promoting the importance of immunization.</narrative>
  </description>
